	</script><div style="opacity:0" class="sc-gWXbKe hoZTIr __pf" id="__pf"><div data-pf-type="Body" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf pf-1_"><div data-pf-type="Layout" class="sc-XxNYO kddAeL pf-2_"><div data-section-id="pf-89cf" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bQtKYq fbyRgD pf-3_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-jHkVzv dyVEVs"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-4_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-5_"><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-6_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-8_">Mil Hodgson – 13/04/2022</span></p><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-9_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-11_">6 Best Moisturisers &amp; SPF For Men With Dry Skin (2022)</span></h1><div data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-evcjhq dAUdgU pf-12_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/6784/9368/t/14/assets/dry-skin-1649844685289.webp?v=1649844687" width="800" height="540"/></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-13_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-14_"><p class="sc-fmBCVi kcDJKd pf-15_ dropcap--none" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Dropcap" class="sc-lkgTHX cqBkDW pf-16_">D</span><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-17_">id you know that dry skin is commonly mistaken for dehydrated skin? They might sound similar, but the two aren’t the same − confusing, right? They have different signs, causes, and methods of treatment. Not sure how you can tell the difference? Read on and find out.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-18_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-20_">Dry vs Dehydrated Skin</span></h2><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-21_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-23_">So, how can you tell if your skin is dry or dehydrated? These terms are often used interchangeably, but they’re different from one another. Dry skin that once glowed might just be dehydrated, while skin that’s considered dehydrated could instead be affected by deep-set dryness. It’s important to be able to identify which kind you have, so you can determine what treatment and products are best to use.<br><br><b>Dry skin lacks oil</b>, which causes it to look <b>drier</b> and <b>flakier</b> in appearance. As a result, you might experience <b>redness</b> and <b>irritation</b>. It’s also worth noting that (unlike dehydrated skin) <b>dry skin is classed as a skin type</b> − much like oily and combination skin. Although it can’t be completely fixed, it can be improved. This can be done with nourishing moisturisers, which will replace the oils that your skin isn’t producing.<br><br><b>Dehydrated skin</b>, on the other hand, <b>is seriously lacking in H2O</b>. It’s a condition that can affect people with any skin type, and it causes the <b>skin to look duller and flat</b>. This is due to surface cell deflation; <b>the cells aren’t being held up because there isn’t any moisture in them</b>. Your face can feel tighter, and you may notice small, triangular fine lines on your skin. Not ideal!<br><br>One way to check if your skin is dehydrated is to do the <b>pinch test</b>. Pinch a small amount of skin over the back of your hand, your abdomen, or your chest, and hold it for a few seconds. If your <b>skin doesn’t bounce back immediately, then the likelihood is that you’re dehydrated.</b> <b>Drinking water</b> throughout the day will keep you hydrated, but you can also use <b>hydrating serums and <a href="/blogs/the-humans-of-humanery-journal/best-face-mists-for-men-2022" target="_self">face mists</a></b> to top up your moisture and give you bouncy skin.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-24_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-26_">Moisturisers For Dry Skin</span></h2><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-27_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-29_">When looking for moisturisers to treat dry skin, you’ll want to keep an eye out for the following ingredients. Some of these words might be unfamiliar or intimidating to you, but don’t worry, we’ve explained below what each ingredient does along with some examples:<br><br><b>Humectants:</b>&nbsp;These keep your skin hydrated, and will also help you to shed dead skin cells. Common humectants include hyaluronic acid and lactic acid.<br><br><b>Occlusives:</b>&nbsp;These work alongside humectants, going a step further by preventing the loss of moisture. Common occlusives include dimethicone and petrolatum.<br><br><b>Emollients:</b>&nbsp;These fill the cracks that dry skin causes, therefore smoothing and softening the skin. Common emollients include mineral oil and virgin coconut oil.<br><br><b>Ceramides and other anti-ageing ingredients:</b>&nbsp;These help to lock moisture in, and therefore may help reduce the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles.<br><br>You should also <b>look for a</b> <b>moisturiser with SPF</b>. Not only will it keep your face feeling soft and nourished, but it will also improve your skin’s defence against UVA and UVB rays. Sunburn may lead to dry skin, hence using an SPF moisturiser will help you avoid this, and keep your skin protected. The other benefit of using an SPF moisturiser is that it’s essentially doing two jobs in one product.&nbsp;</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-30_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-32_">Added Tips</span></h2><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-35_">To up your skincare and get soft, moisturised skin, consider the following tips:<br><br><b>Moisturise a minute after washing: </b>Applying moisturiser onto damp skin will lock in the moisture and ensure that your skin is well-hydrated.<br><br><b>Use night cream:</b>&nbsp;As well as combating dryness, using a night cream can also boost your collagen production. This will improve the elasticity of your skin, reducing the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles.<br><br><b>Always wear SPF:</b>&nbsp;Regularly using sunscreen is an optimal way of preventing skin damage. It also fights the effects of premature ageing. <br><br><b>Eat a healthy diet:</b>&nbsp;Diets that are high in fat, or contain a lot of sugary foods, can cause skin inflammation; nutrient deficiencies may also contribute to dry skin. Try including <b>sweet potato, avocado, and cod liver oil</b> in your diet to get those extra vitamins.<br><br>So now that you’ve learnt about dry skin, let's explore some products should you use to treat it. Whether you’re looking to add to your current routine, or you’re just starting out, we’ve made it simpler for you to choose.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-36_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-38_">Best Moisturisers &amp; SPF For Dry Skin</span></h2><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-39_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:30px" data-href="/products/buy-heath-moisturiser" data-target="_blank" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-40_"><div data-product-id="7151024308376" data-pf-type="ProductMedia" class="sc-fivaXQ klojpP pf-41_">
